        <hr noshade size="1">
        
        <font color="white" face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica" size="2">"Spelling Errors<BR>First, I want to thank all of you that have been sending in spelling errors. I have a few comments to make about some of the types of comments we've been getting. </P><P>A few people have pointed out that when you use the Hail feature, it creates a sentence like: "Hail Bob." Such a sentence should, we admit, have a comma after the word hail. It should read: "Hail, Bob." </P><P>Unfortunately, changing that would be a real problem. NPCs are trained (through expensive drug therapy) to respond to the existing text, without the comma. Retraining them (which would probably mean intensive electric shock therapy) would require that we change every NPC that responds to that hail text. While perhaps a worthwhile endeavor, we have decided that the grammatical headaches that this causes some people doesn't warrant the time needed to make the change, and the likely bugs and broken quests that would occur. Sorry, but it's going to stay as it is. </P><P>Also, we've had a lot of comments about things on the character creation screens. Those have to be changed by programmers, not designers. We've created an extensive list of changes needed, and the programmers will be fixing them when they get the odd spare moment. That's just going to take time to finish, since it seems more worthwhile to have the programmers working on other things most of the time. </P><P>Otherwise, we are tackling the spelling errors as they come in. Many of the ones you've sent in are already fixed. Thanks for the help in this."<BR>-Absor</P><P></P><P>So my fellow necro's...as you can see.  The people at V.I. are very busy answering questions regarding comas and such...so naturally they have no time left to worry about bugs or class balance issues.  And you thought they wre just lazy!</P><P></P><P><BR>Jaraxel<BR>51 DE Necro<BR>49 Shorty Druid<BR>17 Iksar Monk</P><P>"Life is but a blink of the eye...when compared to the eternity of death....I AM ETERNAL"</font></td>
